FBIS4-68125 "jptot020__l94047" JPRS-TOT-94-020-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 7 May 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL U.S. Tourist Stabbed in W. Bank Village U.S. Tourist Stabbed in W. Bank Village TA0705191494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 7 May 94 TA0705191494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] A 22-year-old American tourist was stabbed in the hand and wounded this afternoon outside the village of Husan, near the settlement of Betar. He was attacked as he was walking alone in the orchards. The stabber, a 17-year-old boy, fled the scene. The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] clamped a curfew on Husan and arrested three suspects.
